Clustering enhanced the regression performance with the validation set, but only slightly Even more performance was achieved by choosing variables for the clustering analysis. Variables were chosen by VIF, by scatterplot, and corrplot. In the scatterplot, variables were chosen that appeared to have a combination of dicrete levels and difference between levels. In the corrplot, variables with fairly high absolute value correlation with other indep. variables were chosen. (3,17,21,23,25,30,31,33,7,16) - RMSE = .1305528 vs.RMSE = .1307519

An elastic net model is attempted with the glmnet to try lasso/ridge regressions. Both shrink the effects of betas. The lasso selects features and does shrinkage. The glmnet mixes between the two models.
